pescador.Streamer class wraps generators for lazy evaluation.
- Streamers can be lazily instantiated (as in joblib.delayed)
- Streamers can be (de)serialized and moved across process boundaries
- max_iter parameter to limit sampling from infinite generators
- cycle() method for infinite sampling of finite generators
- tuples() method for interfacing with Keras

flowRoot.flowPara: Pescador is a library for managing data streams for iterative machine learning algorithms. While many machine learning packages can consume samples provided by generators, practitioners often must write custom code to manage large data sets. Pescador provides a suite of utilities to buffer data, multiplex streams under a variety of different sampling strategies, manage small active working sets, and generate data in parallel processes.
Pescador 1.0 is released under a permissive open source license (ISC), and is supported on Python 2.7 and 3.4/3.5/3.6.

text.tspan: pescador.Mux is a Streamer, and can do all the Streamer things!
- Muxes can be recombined (Mux of Mux)
- Streams can be activated with or without replacement
Mux interleaves samples from multiple Streamers
Only a small active set is kept alive at any time
- Small working set = low memory footprint
- Large working set = better approximation of the full distribution
Streamers are deactivated and replaced at random
- Don't replace all the streams at once
